{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1869,"text":"It's 1878."},{"time":4969,"text":"Sir Francis Galton\ngives a remarkable talk."},{"time":9318,"text":"He's speaking to the anthropologic\ninstitute of Great Britain and Ireland."},{"time":14170,"text":"Known for his pioneering work\nin human intelligence,"},{"time":18220,"text":"Galton is a brilliant polymath."},{"time":21716,"text":"He's an explorer,"},{"time":23294,"text":"an anthropologist,"},{"time":25071,"text":"a sociologist,"},{"time":26625,"text":"a psychologist"},{"time":28218,"text":"and a statistician."},{"time":31387,"text":"He's also a eugenist."},{"time":34600,"text":"In this talk,"},{"time":36807,"text":"he presents a new technique\nby which he can combine photographs"},{"time":41584,"text":"and produce composite portraits."},{"time":44663,"text":"This technique could be used\nto characterize different types of people."},{"time":50702,"text":"Galton thinks that if he combines\nphotographs of violent criminals,"},{"time":56075,"text":"he will discover the face of criminality."},{"time":60253,"text":"But to his surprise,"},{"time":62264,"text":"the composite portrait that he produces"},{"time":65951,"text":"is beautiful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70026,"text":"Galton's surprising finding\nraises deep questions:"},{"time":73515,"text":"What is beauty?"},{"time":76070,"text":"Why do certain configurations of line\nand color and form excite us so?"},{"time":84372,"text":"For most of human history,"},{"time":85924,"text":"these questions have been approached\nusing logic and speculation."},{"time":92115,"text":"But in the last few decades,"},{"time":93656,"text":"scientists have addressed\nthe question of beauty"},{"time":96558,"text":"using ideas from evolutionary psychology\nand tools of neuroscience."},{"time":102502,"text":"We're beginning to glimpse\nthe why and the how of beauty,"},{"time":106945,"text":"at least in terms of what it means\nfor the human face and form."},{"time":111201,"text":"And in the process,"},{"time":112781,"text":"we're stumbling upon some surprises."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116160,"text":"When it comes to seeing\nbeauty in each other,"},{"time":119749,"text":"while this decision is certainly\nsubjective for the individual,"},{"time":124128,"text":"it's sculpted by factors that contribute\nto the survival of the group."},{"time":128810,"text":"Many experiments have shown"},{"time":131482,"text":"that a few basic parameters contribute\nto what makes a face attractive."},{"time":136315,"text":"These include averaging, symmetry\nand the effects of hormones."},{"time":142015,"text":"Let's take each one of these in turn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146531,"text":"Galton's finding"},{"time":148029,"text":"that composite or average faces\nare typically more attractive"},{"time":153336,"text":"than each individual face\nthat contributes to the average"},{"time":156917,"text":"has been replicated many times."},{"time":159933,"text":"This laboratory finding fits\nwith many people's intuitions."},{"time":164754,"text":"Average faces represent\nthe central tendencies of a group."},{"time":169724,"text":"People with mixed features\nrepresent different populations,"},{"time":174067,"text":"and presumably harbor\ngreater genetic diversity"},{"time":177439,"text":"and adaptability to the environment."},{"time":180337,"text":"Many people find mixed-race\nindividuals attractive"},{"time":184765,"text":"and inbred families less so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188627,"text":"The second factor that contributes\nto beauty is symmetry."},{"time":193474,"text":"People generally find symmetric faces\nmore attractive than asymmetric ones."},{"time":198758,"text":"Developmental abnormalities\nare often associated with asymmetries."},{"time":204034,"text":"And in plants, animals and humans,"},{"time":207323,"text":"asymmetries often arise\nfrom parasitic infections."},{"time":211373,"text":"Symmetry, it turns out,"},{"time":213615,"text":"is also an indicator of health."},{"time":218469,"text":"In the 1930s,"},{"time":220779,"text":"a man named Maksymilian Faktorowicz"},{"time":223703,"text":"recognized the importance\nof symmetry for beauty"},{"time":226904,"text":"when he designed the beauty micrometer."},{"time":230297,"text":"With this device,"},{"time":231472,"text":"he could measure minor asymmetric flaws"},{"time":234551,"text":"which he could then make up for\nwith products he sold from his company,"},{"time":239124,"text":"named brilliantly\nafter himself, Max Factor,"},{"time":242972,"text":"which, as you know,\nis one of the world's most famous brands"},{"time":246007,"text":"for \"make up.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":248515,"text":"The third factor that contributes\nto facial attractiveness"},{"time":252497,"text":"is the effect of hormones."},{"time":255533,"text":"And here, I need to apologize\nfor confining my comments"},{"time":260282,"text":"to heterosexual norms."},{"time":263618,"text":"But estrogen and testosterone\nplay important roles"},{"time":268112,"text":"in shaping features\nthat we find attractive."},{"time":271643,"text":"Estrogen produces features\nthat signal fertility."},{"time":276334,"text":"Men typically find women attractive"},{"time":279308,"text":"who have elements\nof both youth and maturity."},{"time":284183,"text":"A face that's too baby-like might\nmean that the girl is not yet fertile,"},{"time":289119,"text":"so men find women attractive"},{"time":291116,"text":"who have large eyes,\nfull lips and narrow chins"},{"time":295376,"text":"as indicators of youth,"},{"time":297700,"text":"and high cheekbones\nas an indicator of maturity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302564,"text":"Testosterone produces features\nthat we regard as typically masculine."},{"time":308777,"text":"These include heavier brows,"},{"time":310821,"text":"thinner cheeks"},{"time":312150,"text":"and bigger, squared-off jaws."},{"time":314426,"text":"But here's a fascinating irony."},{"time":317695,"text":"In many species,"},{"time":318870,"text":"if anything,"},{"time":320275,"text":"testosterone suppresses the immune system."},{"time":325002,"text":"So the idea that testosterone-infused\nfeatures are a fitness indicator"},{"time":329200,"text":"doesn't really make a whole lot of sense."},{"time":332183,"text":"Here, the logic is turned on its head."},{"time":335658,"text":"Instead of a fitness indicator,"},{"time":337831,"text":"scientists invoke a handicap principle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342789,"text":"The most commonly cited\nexample of a handicap"},{"time":346345,"text":"is the peacock's tail."},{"time":348542,"text":"This beautiful but cumbersome tail\ndoesn't exactly help the peacock"},{"time":352962,"text":"avoid predators"},{"time":354910,"text":"and approach peahens."},{"time":357188,"text":"Why should such an extravagant\nappendage evolve?"},{"time":361947,"text":"Even Charles Darwin,"},{"time":364408,"text":"in an 1860 letter to Asa Gray wrote"},{"time":367831,"text":"that the sight of the peacock's tail\nmade him physically ill."},{"time":372144,"text":"He couldn't explain it\nwith his theory of natural selection,"},{"time":375066,"text":"and out of this frustration,"},{"time":376989,"text":"he developed the theory\nof sexual selection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381501,"text":"On this account,"},{"time":382675,"text":"the display of the peacock's tail\nis about sexual enticement,"},{"time":387082,"text":"and this enticement means\nit's more likely the peacock will mate"},{"time":393328,"text":"and have offspring."},{"time":395818,"text":"Now, the modern twist\non this display argument"},{"time":399472,"text":"is that the peacock is also\nadvertising its health to the peahen."},{"time":406001,"text":"Only especially fit organisms\ncan afford to divert resources"},{"time":411152,"text":"to maintaining such\nan extravagant appendage."},{"time":414592,"text":"Only especially fit men can afford\nthe price that testosterone levies"},{"time":419509,"text":"on their immune system."},{"time":421560,"text":"And by analogy, think of the fact"},{"time":424242,"text":"that only very rich men can afford\nto pay more than $10,000 for a watch"},{"time":431231,"text":"as a display of their financial fitness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435113,"text":"Now, many people hear these kinds\nof evolutionary claims"},{"time":437939,"text":"and think they mean that we somehow\nare unconsciously seeking mates"},{"time":443693,"text":"who are healthy."},{"time":445632,"text":"And I think this idea\nis probably not right."},{"time":450269,"text":"Teenagers and young adults are not exactly\nknown for making decisions"},{"time":455155,"text":"that are predicated on health concerns."},{"time":458544,"text":"But they don't have to be,"},{"time":460169,"text":"and let me explain why."}]},{"cues":[{"time":463151,"text":"Imagine a population"},{"time":465208,"text":"in which people have three different\nkinds of preferences:"},{"time":469410,"text":"for green, for orange and for red."},{"time":473922,"text":"From their point of view,"},{"time":475137,"text":"these preferences have\nnothing to do with health;"},{"time":477524,"text":"they just like what they like."},{"time":480128,"text":"But if it were also the case\nthat these preferences are associated"},{"time":484193,"text":"with the different likelihood\nof producing offspring --"},{"time":487215,"text":"let's say in a ratio of 3:2:1 --"},{"time":491060,"text":"then in the first generation,"},{"time":492528,"text":"there would be 3 greens\nto 2 oranges to 1 red,"},{"time":495824,"text":"and in each subsequent generation,"},{"time":498034,"text":"the proportion of greens increase,"},{"time":502067,"text":"so that in 10 generations,"},{"time":503802,"text":"98 percent of this population\nhas a green preference."},{"time":507963,"text":"Now, a scientist coming in\nand sampling this population"},{"time":511108,"text":"discovers that green\npreferences are universal."},{"time":515606,"text":"So the point about this little\nabstract example"},{"time":519502,"text":"is that while preferences\nfor specific physical features"},{"time":524186,"text":"can be arbitrary for the individual,"},{"time":528090,"text":"if those features are heritable"},{"time":533232,"text":"and they are associated\nwith a reproductive advantage,"},{"time":537415,"text":"over time,"},{"time":538653,"text":"they become universal for the group."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543172,"text":"So what happens in the brain\nwhen we see beautiful people?"},{"time":550520,"text":"Attractive faces activate\nparts of our visual cortex"},{"time":554572,"text":"in the back of the brain,"},{"time":556541,"text":"an area called the fusiform gyrus,"},{"time":558507,"text":"that is especially tuned\nto processing faces,"},{"time":561333,"text":"and an adjacent area called\nthe lateral occipital complex,"},{"time":565371,"text":"that is especially attuned\nto processing objects."},{"time":568700,"text":"In addition,"},{"time":570120,"text":"attractive faces activate parts\nof our reward and pleasure centers"},{"time":575222,"text":"in the front and deep in the brain,"},{"time":578179,"text":"and these include areas\nthat have complicated names,"},{"time":581327,"text":"like the ventral striatum,"},{"time":583215,"text":"the orbitofrontal cortex"},{"time":585158,"text":"and the ventromedial prefrontal cortex."},{"time":588732,"text":"Our visual brain that is tuned\nto processing faces"},{"time":592740,"text":"interacts with our pleasure centers"},{"time":595401,"text":"to underpin the experience of beauty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599719,"text":"Amazingly, while we all\nengage with beauty,"},{"time":603835,"text":"without our knowledge,"},{"time":605456,"text":"beauty also engages us."},{"time":608478,"text":"Our brains respond to attractive faces"},{"time":611001,"text":"even when we're not thinking about beauty."},{"time":614637,"text":"We conducted an experiment\nin which people saw a series of faces,"},{"time":618950,"text":"and in one condition,"},{"time":620677,"text":"they had to decide if a pair of faces\nwere the same or a different person."},{"time":627907,"text":"Even in this condition,"},{"time":630424,"text":"attractive faces drove neural activity\nrobustly in their visual cortex,"},{"time":636590,"text":"despite the fact that they were thinking\nabout a person's identity"},{"time":640127,"text":"and not their beauty."},{"time":643127,"text":"Another group similarly found\nautomatic responses to beauty"},{"time":647462,"text":"within our pleasure centers."},{"time":650551,"text":"Taken together, these studies suggest"},{"time":654033,"text":"that our brain automatically\nresponds to beauty"},{"time":658568,"text":"by linking vision and pleasure."},{"time":661854,"text":"These beauty detectors, it seems,"},{"time":664258,"text":"ping every time we see beauty,"},{"time":666120,"text":"regardless of whatever else\nwe might be thinking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671022,"text":"We also have a \"beauty is good\"\nstereotype embedded in the brain."},{"time":677712,"text":"Within the orbitofrontal cortex,"},{"time":679963,"text":"there's overlapping neural activity"},{"time":681762,"text":"in response to beauty and to goodness,"},{"time":687185,"text":"and this happens even when people\naren't explicitly thinking"},{"time":690731,"text":"about beauty or goodness."},{"time":693906,"text":"Our brains seem to reflexively\nassociate beauty and good."},{"time":698690,"text":"And this reflexive association\nmay be the biologic trigger"},{"time":702692,"text":"for the many social effects of beauty."},{"time":706057,"text":"Attractive people receive\nall kinds of advantages in life."},{"time":711556,"text":"They're regarded as more intelligent,"},{"time":714334,"text":"more trustworthy,"},{"time":715961,"text":"they're given higher pay\nand lesser punishments,"},{"time":719530,"text":"even when such judgments\nare not warranted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":723572,"text":"These kinds of observations\nreveal beauty's ugly side."},{"time":727796,"text":"In my lab, we recently found"},{"time":729893,"text":"that people with minor facial\nanomalies and disfigurements"},{"time":734839,"text":"are regarded as less good, less kind,"},{"time":738647,"text":"less intelligent, less competent\nand less hardworking."},{"time":743854,"text":"Unfortunately, we also have\na \"disfigured is bad\" stereotype."},{"time":750398,"text":"This stereotype is probably\nexploited and magnified"},{"time":757080,"text":"by images in popular media,"},{"time":759517,"text":"in which facial disfigurement\nis often used as a shorthand"},{"time":763437,"text":"to depict someone of villainous character."},{"time":767378,"text":"We need to understand\nthese kinds of implicit biases"},{"time":770856,"text":"if we are to overcome them"},{"time":772617,"text":"and aim for a society\nin which we treat people fairly,"},{"time":776322,"text":"based on their behavior and not\non the happenstance of their looks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":784758,"text":"Let me leave you with one final thought."},{"time":789044,"text":"Beauty is a work in progress."},{"time":792527,"text":"The so-called universal\nattributes of beauty"},{"time":795758,"text":"were selected for during the almost\ntwo million years of the Pleistocene."},{"time":801944,"text":"Life was nasty, brutish\nand a very long time ago."},{"time":808014,"text":"The selection criteria\nfor reproductive success from that time"},{"time":813362,"text":"doesn't really apply today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":815966,"text":"For example,"},{"time":817480,"text":"death by parasite is not one\nof the top ways that people die,"},{"time":821571,"text":"at least not in the technologically\ndeveloped world."},{"time":825997,"text":"From antibiotics to surgery,"},{"time":828381,"text":"birth control to in vitro fertilization,"},{"time":831897,"text":"the filters for reproductive success\nare being relaxed."},{"time":835956,"text":"And under these relaxed conditions,"},{"time":838635,"text":"preference and trait combinations\nare free to drift"},{"time":842893,"text":"and become more variable."},{"time":845416,"text":"Even as we are profoundly\naffecting our environment,"},{"time":850985,"text":"modern medicine\nand technological innovation"},{"time":854322,"text":"is profoundly affecting"},{"time":856099,"text":"the very essence of what it means\nto look beautiful."},{"time":861197,"text":"The universal nature of beauty is changing"},{"time":863771,"text":"even as we're changing the universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":868863,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":870072,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}